{{Infobox storm | name = | image = | alt = | caption = | formed = | active = | dissipated = | lowest pressure = | lowest temperature = | tornadoes = | fujitascale = F3 | tornado duration = | highest winds = | gusts = | maximum snow = | power outages = | total fatalities = | damages = | affected = | location = Bouctouche, New Brunswick | current advisories = | enhanced = | notes = }} The '''1879 Bouctouche Tornado''' was a tornado that struck the town of [[Bouctouche, New Brunswick]] on Wednesday, August 6, 1879.
It is estimated that the tornado was an [[Fujita scale|F3]] in strength, and is the easternmost ''major'' tornado in [[North America]], though weaker tornadoes and [[waterspout]]s have been known to form in [[Prince Edward Island]] and [[Nova Scotia]].
The tornado killed 5&nbsp;people, injured 10 others, and rendered 25&nbsp;families homeless.
