'''Andrew Paul Hendry''' is an American/Canadian Professor of [[evolution]] [[biology]] and [[ecology]] at [[McGill University]].
==Early life and career== Andrew Hendry was born on March 24, 1968 in [[Woodland, California]]. In June 1991 he graduated Bachelor of Science degree from the [[University of Victoria]] and four years later obtained his Master's from [[University of Washington]]. Three years later, the same institution granted him a PhD. From 1998 to 2000 he worked at the Department of Zoology of the [[University of British Columbia]], From 1999 to 2002 he was a Darwin Postdoctoral Fellow at the [[University of Massachusetts Amherst]]. Andrew Hendry is an editor of numerous scientific journals including ''[[Journal of Evolutionary Biology]]'', ''[[Evolution (journal)|Evolution]]'', ''Biological Invasions'' and ''Evolutionary Ecology''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://redpath-staff.mcgill.ca/hendry/CVHendry.pdf|title=Andrew Paul Hendry|accessdate=March 6, 2018}}</ref>
==Works== *2004 - Evolution Illuminated: Salmon and Their Relatives *2017 - Eco-evolutionary Dynamics
