[[File:Dowelmax.jpg|thumb|300px|right|The Dowelmax Jig with distance gauge bar]]
The '''Dowelmax''' is a loose tenon [[dowel]]ling jig manufactured by the O.M.S. Tool company in [[Canada]]. The manufacturer claims that the small [[Engineering tolerance|manufacturing tolerances]] of {{convert|0.026|mm|in}} for the [[aluminium]], [[brass]] and [[steel]] components of the jig ensure accuracy and repeatability. The precision manufacturing adds to the unit's cost, which is higher than other dowelling jigs.

The tool allows the placement of five dowels in one pass. A distance gauge bar provided with the jig allows accurate spacing between sets of dowels.

==Joint strength==
Tests by both the manufacturer,<ref name="dmtest">{{Cite web|url=http://www.dowelmax.com/jointstrength.html|title=Destructive Tests Comparing Biscuit Joints, Mortise and Tenon Joints, and Multiple Dowel Joints made with Dowelmax|accessdate=2008-08-01|publisher=O.M.S Tool Company}}</ref> and [[Wood magazine]],<ref name="woodmag">{{Cite web|url=http://www.woodstore.net/is17ju201.html|title=What’s what in loose-tenon tools|accessdate=2008-08-01|publisher=Wood Magazine|date=2007-07-01|work=issue 177}}</ref> are claimed to show that dowel joints made with the Dowelmax are stronger than most other woodworking joints tested.

In 2007, ''Wood'' magazine compared the joint strength of various loose tenon methods and tools, with these results:<ref name="woodmag" />

A 2011 review<ref name="dmtest2011">{{Cite web|url=http://toolreviews.woodmagazine.com/power-tools/joinery-tools-jigs/doweling-mortising-jigs/discussions/review?id=102|title=Review-A-Tool Dowelmax Doweling Jig|accessdate=2014-10-07|publisher=WOOD Magazine}}</ref> by [http://www.woodmagazine.com/ Wood Magazine], has rated [http://www.dowelmax.com/ Dowelmax] very highly as a dowel joinery tool. The review classifies Dowelmax as "the best dowelling jig ever made".

