{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}} {{See also|List of environmental ministries}} An '''environment minister''' (sometimes '''minister of the environment''' or '''secretary of the environment''') is a [[Cabinet (government)|cabinet]] position charged with protecting the [[natural environment]] and promoting [[wildlife conservation]]. The areas associated with the duties of an ''environmental minister'' depends largely of the needs of an individual countries or states.
The world's first minister of the environment was the British Politician [[Peter Walker, Baron Walker of Worcester|Peter Walker]] from the [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative Party]]. He was appointed in 1970.
