{{Notability|Organizations|date=March 2011}}

The '''World Council for Renewable Energy''' defends, develops, and promotes policies on the multinational, governmental, regional and individual levels in favor of the use of natural and [[renewable energy|renewable forms of energy]] to replace [[fossil fuels|fossil]] and [[nuclear power|nuclear energy]].<ref>[http://www.wcre.de/en/images/downloads/folder_WCRE-eng.pdf World Council for Renewable Energy]</ref>

[[Hermann Scheer]] was the general chairman of the Council.<ref>[http://www.dea.org.au/node/144 Book Review: Energy Autonomy. The economic, social and technological case for renewable energy]</ref>  He died in October 2010.

